io.sphere.sdk.categories.queries

Interface CategoryQuery

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExpansionPathContainer<Category>, MetaModelExpansionDsl<Category,CategoryQuery,CategoryExpansionModel<Category>>, MetaModelQueryDsl<Category,CategoryQuery,CategoryQueryModel,CategoryExpansionModel<Category>>, Query<Category>, QueryDsl<Category,CategoryQuery>, ReferenceExpansionDsl<Category,CategoryQuery>, ReferenceExpansionSupport<Category>, ResourceQuery<Category>, SphereRequest<PagedQueryResult<Category>>

    public interface CategoryQuery
extends MetaModelQueryDsl<Category,CategoryQuery,CategoryQueryModel,CategoryExpansionModel<Category>>
    Provides a QueryDsl for categories to formulate predicates, search expressions and reference expansion path expressions.

    For further information how to use the query API to consult the Query API documentation.

    withCategory(client(), category -> {
    final String externalId = category.getExternalId();

    final Query<Category> query = CategoryQuery.of().byExternalId(externalId);

    final Category actual = client().executeBlocking(query).head().get();
    assertThat(actual).isEqualTo(category);
});

    See the test code.

      • plusExpansionPaths

        CategoryQuery plusExpansionPaths(java.util.function.Function<CategoryExpansionModel<Category>,ExpansionPathContainer<Category>> m)
        Description copied from interface: MetaModelExpansionDsl
        Creates a new object with the properties of the old object but adds a new expansion path to it by using meta models.

        An example in the product projection context:

        final ProductProjectionByIdGet fetch1 = ProductProjectionByIdGet.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT)
        .plusExpansionPaths(m -> m.categories());
assertThat(fetch1.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));

final ProductProjectionByIdGet fetch2 = fetch1.plusExpansionPaths(m -> m.productType());
assertThat(fetch2.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]"), ExpansionPath.of("productType")))
        .isEqualTo(listOf(fetch1.expansionPaths(), ExpansionPath.of("productType")));

//this is equivalent to

final ExpansionPath<ProductProjection> categoryExpand = ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().categories().expansionPaths().get(0);
final ExpansionPath<ProductProjection> productTypeExpand = ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().productType().expansionPaths().get(0);
final ProductProjectionByIdGet fetchB = ProductProjectionByIdGet.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT)
                .withExpansionPaths(asList(categoryExpand, productTypeExpand));
assertThat(fetchB.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]"), ExpansionPath.of("productType")));

        See the test code.
        Specified by:
        plusExpansionPaths in interface MetaModelExpansionDsl<Category,CategoryQuery,CategoryExpansionModel<Category>>

        Returns:

      • withExpansionPaths

        CategoryQuery withExpansionPaths(java.util.function.Function<CategoryExpansionModel<Category>,ExpansionPathContainer<Category>> m)
        Description copied from interface: MetaModelExpansionDsl
        Creates a new object with the properties of the old object but replaces all expansion paths with a single expansionPath by using meta models.

        An example in the product projection context:

        final ProductProjectionByIdGet fetch = ProductProjectionByIdGet.of("id", ProductProjectionType.CURRENT)
                .plusExpansionPaths(ProductProjectionExpansionModel.of().categories());

assertThat(fetch.expansionPaths())
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));

final ProductProjectionByIdGet fetch2 =
        fetch.withExpansionPaths(m -> m.productType());

assertThat(fetch.expansionPaths()).overridingErrorMessage("old object is unchanged")
        .isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("categories[*]")));
assertThat(fetch2.expansionPaths()).isEqualTo(asList(ExpansionPath.of("productType")));
assertThat(fetch2).isNotSameAs(fetch);

        See the test code.
        Specified by:
        withExpansionPaths in interface MetaModelExpansionDsl<Category,CategoryQuery,CategoryExpansionModel<Category>>
        Parameters:
        m - function to use the meta model for expansions to create an expansion path
        Returns:
        new object
